There are bugs and plants.

Both contain energy, and the environment itself contains energy, too.

A bug has two move-thingies. They can push him forward, and also rotate him. Like the two tires of a tank.
However, moving costs energy, and thus, when moving, the bug gives energy to the environment.
The bug has three (?) light sensors, which can see far, but only IF there is something, not WHAT. Two (?) feeling antennas, which can feel and give information about the thing that lies in front of it, but only when it is near to the bug.
